FBIS4-37794 "drnes122_s_94006" FBIS-NES-94-122 Daily Report 23 Jun 1994 Iran Reaction to Mashhad Bombing Continues Reaction to Mashhad Bombing Continues Delegation Postpones Baghdad Trip LD2306184994 Tehran IRNA in English 1758 GMT 23 Jun 94 LD2306184994 Tehran IRNA English BFN [Text] Tehran, June 23, IRNA -- A scheduled visit to Baghdad this Saturday [25 June] of an Iranian foreign ministry delegation has been postponed without indefinitely. [sentence as received] The postponement, according to a foreign ministry spokesman here tonight, is due to the terrorist bomb blast at the holy shrine of Imam Reza (as) in Mashhad on Monday last that took the lives of 26 mourners on the day of Ashura (martyrdom anniversary of Imam Hussein) and injured about 170 others. The terrorist Mujahidden Khalq outfit (MKO) has been held responsible for the blast. The visit to Baghdad was within the framework of pending matters between Tehran and Baghdad.
